"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601148","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-18","<p>The involvement of judges in outside organisations is covered by the Guide to Judicial Conduct, which is published by the independent judiciary. The guide is publicly available on gov.uk. The Department does not discuss the application of this guidance to individual cases.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-10-18T09:32:08.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601148/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601148/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601148/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-13","Muslim Arbitration Tribunal: Judges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what discussions her Department has had with the Judicial Office on permitting district judges to sit as presiding judges at the Muslim Arbitration Tribunal.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","48560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601150","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-18","<p>Prisons should be places of safety and reform. Improving safety and decreasing violence is an urgent priority for the Government.</p><p> </p><p>Prison officers are some our finest public servants. We do not underestimate the challenges faced by everyone working in prisons. We will continue to support our staff to help them maintain safe and secure prisons.</p><p>Funding of £14 million will be given to 10 prisons with some of the highest rates of violence for additional staff to implement new offender management arrangements, including dedicated prisoner contact time.</p><p> </p><p>We will be setting out our plans for prison safety and reform in a White Paper in the coming weeks, including our plans to reduce prison violence.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-18T14:24:12.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601150/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601150/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/601150/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-13","Prison Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps she is taking to improve the safety of prison staff at work.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","48599"
