"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/600619","Department for Education","false","2016-10-20","<p>The information requested is not available without disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Data provided by the Student Loans Company (SLC) shows that the 113,600 English student loan borrowers who were known to be overseas at the beginning of the financial year 2016-17 had a total loan balance of £1.6 billion. Statistics covering English student loan borrowers are published annually by the SLC in the Statistical First Release (SFR) ‘Student Loans in England’.</p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/student-loans-debt-and-repayment/england.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/student-loans-debt-and-repayment/england.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on the repayment status of English student loan borrowers who have become liable to repay (by repayment cohort) can be found in table 3A of the SFR.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-20T16:41:38.01Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/600619/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/600619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/600619/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-12","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the value is of outstanding student loan debts owed by graduates who have moved overseas since 2006.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","48221"
